BURGUNDY

This ancient province of France boasts an equally ancient fame for its great wines, and in the opinion of many connoisseurs, they have no equal. Characterized by a full-bodied, rich flavor, fragrant bouquet and a deep ruby color, the red wines are highly prized and sought after by gourmets the world over. The white wines are dry, vigorous and acknowledged as the finest in France.

The great difficulty confronting the buyer of Burgundies is the bewildering array of wines bearing the same name, but having no resemblance to each other in quality. This is due to the fact that the vineyards of Burgundy are parcelled out among many owners, some of them growers, others traders, and not all of these make the wine which carries the name of their vineyard. There- fore in Burgundy, the important factor is the integrity of the grower and the dealer from whom the wine is obtained.
